  "text": "An open TCP connection can be disconnected when its associated NAT (network address translation) entry is removed from the NAT table of the mobile network carrier [CITATION_1] . This, however, is an easily resolvable issue. The carrier can simply postpone the removal of NAT entries associated with the semi-persistent connections since the semipersistent connection is a carrier-supported feature to provide better web browsing experience to its customers.",
